{
  "answer": "**1. In-Depth User Understanding:** The Prophet deeply understood the customary habits of his people, such as the Quraish who used to swear oaths by their fathers [1]. To elevate their spiritual journey, he directly addressed and corrected this specific behavior [1].\n\n**2. Robust and Enduring Framework:** To protect the resilient foundation of pure faith, he established an unwavering rule, commanding that \"If anybody has to take an oath, he should swear only by Allah\" [1]. \n\n**3. Elegant and Lucid Presentation:** This prohibition is presented with ultimate clarity and grace in Sahih al-Bukhari, where the Prophet explicitly instructs, \"Whoever has to take an oath should swear by Allah or remain silent\" [2]. \n\n**4. Seamless and Accessible Experience:** This provides an exceptionally easy and accessible framework for all believers to follow; by giving the simple option to either swear by the Creator or hold one's peace, it seamlessly prevents individuals from swearing by anything other than Allah [1, 2].",
